                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid vermilion).</seg>
                        Scribe: Walda Śǝllāse. The scribe’s
                        name Walda Śǝllāse is mentioned in the supplication formula in <locus target="#78rb">78rb</locus>.<date>19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the second part of names of the donor
                           and the scribe; some lines in the incipit page of the text alternating
                           with black lines; two initial lines of all sections; the word salām
                           “peace”; the initial word for the ʾarke; elements of punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#84v">f. 84v</locus>
                           <desc>: Magic prayer against the destruction of harvest by hail.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#84v">84v</locus>: በስመ፡ አብ፡ በል፡ ጸሎተ፡ በረድ፡ ምድምያስ፡ ፫ጊዜ … </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#84v">84v</locus>: Pray “Ba-sǝmä ʾAb“ recite “ṣalota
                              bäräd mǝdǝmyas” three times … </quote>
                           <note> Crude written in violet ink, partly unreadable. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Writing exercises: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1v,
                           2r, 2v.
 - Pen trial in <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>. 
 - Name
                           of the donor(?) are erased on some fols. e.g. 3ra, 16ra, 25ra.
 - A
                           note is washed out: <locus target="#84rb">84rb</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings are indicated by the names of the
                              months written in the upper margins: - zä-Ḫǝdar (<locus target="#3r">fol. 3r</locus>) - zä-Taḫśaś (fols. 10v) - mǝnbab zä-Ṭǝrr (<locus target="#17v">fol. 17v</locus>) - zä-Yäkkatit (<locus target="#27r">fol. 27r</locus>) - zä-Mäggabit (<locus target="#31v">fol.
                                 31v</locus>) - zä-Miyāzyā (<locus target="#49v">fol. 49v</locus>) -
                              zä-Gǝnbot (<locus target="#56v">fol. 56v</locus>) - zä-Säne (<locus target="#59v">fol. 59v</locus>) - zä-Ḥamle (<locus target="#64v">fol. 64v</locus>) - zä-Näḥase (<locus target="#69r">fol.
                                 69r</locus>) - zä-Maskaram (<locus target="#72r">fol. 72r</locus>)
                              - zä-Ṭǝqǝmt (<locus target="#74v">fol. 74v</locus>) - zä-Ḫǝdar (<locus target="#78v">fol. 78v</locus>) - zä-Taḫśaś (fols. 79r) - mǝnbab
                              zä-Ṭǝrr (<locus target="#80r">fol. 80r</locus>) - zä-Yäkkatit (<locus target="#80r">fol. 80r</locus>) - zä-Mäggabit (<locus target="#80v">fol. 80v</locus>) - zä-Miyāzyā (<locus target="#81r">fol.
                                 81r</locus>) - zä-Gǝnbot (<locus target="#81r">fol. 81r</locus>) -
                              zä-Säne (<locus target="#81v">fol. 81v</locus>) - zä-Ḥamle (<locus target="#82v">fol. 82v</locus>) - zä-Näḥase (<locus target="#83r">fol. 83r</locus>) - zä-Maskaram (<locus target="#83r">fol.
                                 83r</locus>) - zä-Ṭǝqǝmt (<locus target="#83v">fol.
                              83v</locus>)</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
